  "tacticalAnalysis": {
    "ECU": "Ecuador set up in a compact 4-4-2, sitting deep (28% low block) and looking to exploit Germany on the counter. Remarkably effective despite only 39% possession — two well-taken goals from clinical moments in transition. ANGULO's early equaliser and PLATA's 78th-minute winner were the products of direct, pacey attacks through the lines. Pedro VITE was tireless in midfield, covering more ground than any ECU player and providing vital link-play. The defensive unit held firm under heavy German pressure, with ORDONEZ and PACHO commanding at the back.",
    "GER": "Germany dominated possession (51%) and created 11 shots but were wasteful in front of goal. SANE's early strike suggested a comfortable night, but Ecuador's physical pressing and clinical finishing turned the match. KIMMICH and PAVLOVIC initially controlled midfield before the early Pavlovic substitution disrupted rhythm. RAUM was active on the left with 9 crosses but few found their target. Despite 114 line breaks completed, the final delivery lacked precision — a costly lesson in efficiency."
  },

